duties_responsibilities.duty: Provide advanced technical support and assistance to departments, faculty, and staff for multiple types of systems across the enterprise.
Conduct analysis of specification requirements for an area and/or unit.
Advise and contribute to specialty technical and non-technical knowledge and skills in support of area and unit information resources.
Assist enterprise management on aspects of IT management for area and unit business operations.
Manage team members and/or project leads.
Adhere to all appropriate Institutional policies (including IT OPs) and other relevant internal departmental policies.

education_certification.credential: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, MIS, IT, or other related area (Master's preferred) plus nine (9) years of related full-time paid experience.
